Package: liondown
Title: An updated R Markdown thesis template using the bookdown package
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Chester", "Ismay", email = "chester.ismay@gmail.com", role = c("cre", "aut")),
    person("Nick", "Solomon", email = "nick@nicksolomon.me", role = "aut"),
    person("Jared", "Sampson", email = "jared.sampson@columbia.edu", role="aut"))
Description: Using the bookdown package and LaTeX and Word thesis templates
    from Reed College and Columbia University, this package aims to encourage
    reproducible research using simple Markdown syntax while embedding all of
    the R code to produce plots and analyses as well.
Maintainer: Jared Sampson <jared.sampson@columbia.edu>
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.0)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    bookdown,
    knitr,
    here
Suggests:
    remotes,
    usethis
